Insert your Prompt her. For the most accurate experience remove all weighting. You can drag the output of a textfield onto this textfield.  Enjoy. :)

The Prompt Refiner Light
Serves u as an intuitive interface to enter your positive and your negative prompt.
You simply connect the clip input to it and take the positive and the negative condition from the node and connect it to the KSampler.
The window can be Minimized and maximized again saving Your Prompt state.
the window is draggable so u can leave the node behind and work with the input from where ever u want.

Enjoy 😁

The Prompt Splitter
If u feel like u want to give the specific parts of your prompt some stronger influences in the image, try to split your prompt up in separate "Token"
eg.
Positive Prompt:
An apple, on a tree, realistic, wide shot,
masterpiece, detailed, soft lighting

Negative Prompt:
watermark, text, logo, signature, red, bad quality, bad lighting

Enjoy 😁

The Text Weight
Use it as a simple Text/Prompt input and give the entire content a weight from 0-2
0 having the least influence on your image while 2 is the highest influence. 1 is the standard value applying to all token no matter if u weight them or not.

Tip
if u convert the input field to an input "nozzle" u can attach any text input and weight that content

Enjoy 😁

The Condition Funnel
This node collects all your text inputs
transforms it into the conditioning a KSampler needs and u can then use it as a positive or negative for your image generation.

Tip
You can also use this node in combination with the Prompt Fusion node to seperate the different parts of your prompt into Categories and then Fuse them into a single positive prompt. More about this in the "Category Setup" - Workflow

Enjoy 😁

The Style Agent
This is your catalogue node to get a variety of Styles for image generations.

Note that the higher your tier the bigger the style catalogue

PS: if your catalogue is not loading automatically just chose the directory manually.

ComfyUI\custom_nodes\FoW_Suite_LIGHT\data\Library


Enjoy 😁

The Prompt Fusion 
The 2 Prompt Fusion nodes serve the same purpose,
they fuse your dissected prompt into their respective Positive and Negative parts so u have a single output for the Ksampler.

Note: Remember the hole purpose of this suite is to enhance your prompt and that means to split it up and put it back together


Enjoy 😁

If the content u are looking for is not within the Catalogue,
here is a little workaround.

Add a text input or a clip text encoder node to the weight node and type in your desired value manually

Enjoy 😁
